        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 7:59PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 759 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bridger moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crow Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
